messages.content: How can you make the phrase “full cash” into a 7 letter phrase

The phrase "full cash" already consists of 9 letters. To transform it into a 7-letter phrase while retaining a meaning similar to the original would be challenging since removing any letters without substituting others would typically result in a phrase that does not convey the concept of "full cash."

However, if you allow for a change in wording while preserving the essence of the original phrase, one option could be "all cash," which signifies that a transaction could be made entirely in cash. This still does not give us 7 letters.

To create a 7-letter phrase, we can use the word "paidout" which suggests that cash has been distributed in full for a particular purpose, although this is not a direct synonym for "full cash." It is a bit of a stretch, but with these constraints, it is difficult to get a perfect synonym.
